Example data for RedoxRRI

Source: R/data-redoxrri_example.R
redoxrri_example.Rd

A small simulated dataset bundled with RedoxRRI to demonstrate the full workflow of computing the Holobiont Redox Resilience Index (RRI) and visualizing plant–soil–microbe contributions.

Format

A named list with components:

ROS_flux

data.frame; samples (rows) by plant physiological traits (columns).

Eh_stability

data.frame; samples (rows) by soil redox variables (columns).

micro_data

data.frame; samples (rows) by microbial features (columns).

graph

An igraph object representing a microbial association network.

id

data.frame; sample metadata (plot, depth, time).

Source

Simulated data generated for examples and unit tests.

Details

This dataset is synthetic and intended solely for:

  • Function examples

  • Unit tests

  • Vignettes and tutorials '

Values are generated to mimic realistic structure:

  • Multivariate plant physiological traits (e.g. Fv/Fm, NPQ)

  • Soil redox chemistry gradients (Eh, Fe/Mn ratios)

  • High-dimensional, sparse microbial abundance data

  • A system-level microbial association network

The data do not represent any real biological system.

res <- rri_pipeline_st(
  ROS_flux = redoxrri_example$ROS_flux,
  Eh_stability = redoxrri_example$Eh_stability,
  micro_data = redoxrri_example$micro_data,
  graph = redoxrri_example$graph,
  id = redoxrri_example$id,
  group_cols = c("plot", "depth"),
  scale_by = c("plot", "depth"),
  direction_phys = "auto",
  direction_anchor_phys = "FvFm",
  direction_soil = "auto",
  direction_anchor_soil = "Eh"
)
